OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779296759
OL,3,CFuel duty increase to be scrapped,
OL,4,Csays Starmer
OL,6,FSir Keir Starmer has announced help
OL,7,Ffor motorists faced with rising fuel
OL,8,Fprices as a result of the war in Iran.
OL,10,FThe prime minister told MPs on
OL,11,FWednesday that the 5p per litre fuel
OL,12,Fduty cut introduced by the
OL,13,FConservative government in March 2022
OL,14,Fwould be extended for the rest of the
OL,15,Fyear.
OL,17,FHe told MPs: "I can announce today
OL,18,Fthat we are giving our hauliers a 12-
OL,19,Fmonth road tax holiday, helping to
OL,20,Fkeep prices down.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779296759
OL,3,CFuel duty increase to be scrapped,
OL,4,Csays Starmer
OL,6,F"And we are backing drivers by
OL,7,Fextending the freeze in fuel duty for
OL,8,Fthe rest of the year."
OL,10,FRates were previously planned to
OL,11,Fincrease from September, gradually
OL,12,Freturning to previous levels over the
OL,13,Fnext five years.
OL,15,FIran's restrictions on tankers passing
OL,16,Fthrough the Strait of Hormuz mean the
OL,17,Faverage price of a litre of petrol and
OL,18,Fdiesel at UK forecourts is 26p and 44p
OL,19,Frespectively more expensive than
OL,20,Fbefore the conflict started on
OL,21,FFebruary 28.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779296759
OL,3,CFuel duty increase to be scrapped,
OL,4,Csays Starmer
OL,6,FThe government estimates this will
OL,7,Fsave the average motorist over #120.
OL,9,FAlongside backtracking on the fuel
OL,10,Fduty increase, the government also
OL,11,Fannounced support for farmers who have
OL,12,Fbeen facing increased costs on
OL,13,Ffertiliser and fuel.
OL,15,FThe government has pledged to cut the
OL,16,Fduty rate on red diesel by over a
OL,17,Fthird per litre from 10.18p to 6.48p,
OL,18,Fthe lowest rate in over 20 years.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779296759
OL,3,CFuel duty increase to be scrapped,
OL,4,Csays Starmer
OL,6,FThis lower rate will take effect from
OL,7,FJune 15 and remain in place until the
OL,8,Fend of the year.
OL,10,FStarmer also announced that hauliers
OL,11,Fwould benefit from a "12-month road
OL,12,Ftax holiday".
OL,14,FThe Treasury said they would pay #1 at
OL,15,Ftheir annual renewal, saving #600 for
OL,16,Fa typical heavy lorry and #912 for the
OL,17,Fbiggest vehicles on the road.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
