FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779296759
OL,3,CFuel duty increase to be scrapped,
OL,4,Csays Starmer
OL,6,FTory leader Kemi Badenoch thanked the
OL,7,FPM for the "U-turn" on fuel duty,
OL,8,Fpointing out her party had been
OL,9,Fcalling on Labour to scrap the rise
OL,10,Ffor some time.
OL,12,FShe told MPs: "I welcome some of what
OL,13,Fthe prime minister has said on fuel
OL,14,Fduty. Yes, it's still a freeze, but we
OL,15,Fasked him about this on the 11th of
OL,16,FMarch and the 25th of March, and he
OL,17,Fsaid he wasn't going to do it.
OL,19,F"So, thank you for the U-turn.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779296759
OL,3,CFuel duty increase to be scrapped,
OL,4,Csays Starmer
OL,6,F"Labour MPs are shaking their heads.
OL,7,FIt would make more sense if they just
OL,8,Fdid what we were doing, because they
OL,9,Fget there in the end anyway."
